Adding CO2 to the air is like throwing another blanket on the bed .
It reduces Earth &apos;s heat radiation to space , so there &apos;s a temporary energy imbalance .
More energy is coming in than going out , until Earth warms up enough to again radiate to space as much energy as it absorbs from the Sun .
So the key quantity is Earth &apos;s energy imbalance .
Is there more energy coming in than going out ?
