I want to end by applying the idea of Middle World to our perceptions of each other .
Most scientists today subscribe to a mechanistic view of the mind : we &apos;re the way we are because our brains are wired up as they are , our hormones are the way they are .
We &apos;d be different , our characters would be different , if our neuro-anatomy and our physiological chemistry were different .
