Nature feeds the heart cells in your body with a very , very dense blood supply .
In the lab , we micro-pattern channels in the biomaterials on which we grow the cells , and this allows us to flow the cell culture media , the cells &apos; food , through the scaffolds where we &apos;re growing the cells — a lot like what you might expect from a capillary bed in the heart .
